<%-- Question 4--%>

<b><a name="Ques4">What is the overall process for developing a channel?</a></b> <br/>

The channel provider refers generally to both the channel developer (who develops the channel assets) and the feed
provider (who provides the channel's data source e.g. weather information).
<br/>

The channel provider must:
<ol>
    <li>Submit a channel concept to Verizon Wireless</li>
    <li>Secure Verizon Wireless approval on the channel concept</li>
    <li>gain access to the Adobe Mobile AppBuilder Program and attent Flash Cast&#0153; training.</li>
    <li>Develop a channel using the Flash&reg; CS3 Professional, Adobe Mobile AppBuilder and Adobe-hosted test server.
    </li>
    <li>Develop the channel data source.</li>
    <li>Complete the Dashboard Channel Submission document.</li>
    <li>Work with Verizon Wireless to determine how often channel content is updated.</li>
    <li>Complete an initial channel validation.</li>
    <li>Submit a final channel for deployment into production.</li>
    <li>Maintain the data source.</li>
</ol>
<a href="#DashboardQuestions">Back To Top</a><br/><br/>

